records.addlTxt:
Defendant Lemar C Thomas in court, in custody, with attorney Joseph Smith.   Barbara A. Michaels appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Plea Colloquy.
Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Count 2 is dismissed and read in.

The Court Orders the Following:

Imposed and Stayed Sentence of:

90 Days  HUBER WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS.  CONSECUTIVE TO 15CM1039

Term of Probation: 2 Years  CONCURRENT TO 15CM1039

Conditions of Probation:
- Absolute Sobriety; Random U.A.s;
- No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
- No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
- Any valid prescription drugs must be taken in the manner in which they are prescribed;
- Inform agent of all prescriptions;
- Sign Medical Release for Agent;
- Obtain a valid driver's license within 6 months;
- Operate a Motor Vehicle with a Valid Drivers License;
- Work on educational opportunities;
- Maintain/Obtain full time employment.
- Provide DNA sample if not yet provided  and pay surcharge

Costs: $243.00 
DNA Surcharge:  $200.00
DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 
(Costs in this case and 15CM1041 to be paid at the rate of $25.00  per month commencing 9-1-15 and/or  69 hours of community service to be completed by completion of probation.  Court must receive notice of completion prior to due date.  Failure to pay or complete community service the Court orders 7 days Huber as contempt for non-compliance with Court Order).

Condition Time: 30 days Huber NON WORKING HOURSE WITH STANDARD RELEASE CONDITIONS -  Stayed and to be used at the agent's discretion
